    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required credibility level for a model risk level 3, medium-consequence COU. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is documented and accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 prescribes a single standard test configuration, and the regulatory submission context does not require multi-condition testing. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the claim that the FEA framework reliably predicts non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending behavior within the declared acceptance bounds. Decision: Accepted.",
